a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. InVideo AI is best suited for YouTube creators, social media video at scale, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Visla, meanwhile, shines for business teams creating video content, screen recording workflows, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, InVideo AI describes itself as \"Generate publish-ready videos from a text prompt.\" Visla, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI video platform for recording, editing, and sharing.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **InVideo AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Visla is a poor choice — far from it. Visla excels in its own right, particularly for business teams creating video content and screen recording workflows.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value full video from single prompt, go with InVideo AI. If good screen recording matters more to you, Visla is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
